Samuel Clemens grew up along the banks of
the Mississippi River, where he eventually

00:06:53.650 --> 00:06:55.689
became a steamboat pilot in 1857.

00:06:55.689 --> 00:07:00.009
It was from his experiences here that he came
up with the name “Mark Twain” sometime

00:07:00.009 --> 00:07:01.630
around 1863.

00:07:01.630 --> 00:07:06.220
This was river slang for 12 feet of water,
or two fathoms, with Mark twain literally

00:07:06.220 --> 00:07:46.449
meaning “mark two” or the second mark
on the depth measurement line.

